pulltitle: Add Mozilla Code of Conduct
pullsbody:
Fixes #68


As of January 1 2019, Mozilla requires that all GitHub projects include this [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](https://github.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) file in the project root. The file has two parts:

1. Required Text - All text under the headings *Community Participation Guidelines and How to Report*, are required, and should not be altered.
2. Optional Text - The Project Specific Etiquette heading provides a space to speak more specifically about ways people can work effectively and inclusively together. Some examples of those can be found on the [Firefox Debugger](https://github.com/devtools-html/debugger.html/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) project, and [Common Voice](https://github.com/mozilla/voice-web/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). (The optional part is commented out in the [raw template file](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md), and will not be visible until you modify and uncomment that part.)

If you have any questions about this file, or Code of Conduct policies and procedures, please see [Mozilla-GitHub-Standards](https://wiki.mozilla.org/GitHub/Repository_Requirements) or email Mozilla-GitHub-Standards+CoC@mozilla.com.

_(Message COC002)_

Add Mozilla Code of Conduct file

Fixes #68.

_(Message COC002)_

pulltitle: Bug 1277653 - Add support for filtering whether tests should be run
pullsbody:
This adds a "run_if_changed" item to runtests section of a test configuration
file. If present, the test will only run if files under those paths were
modified in the revision being tested.

This requires getting the pushlog and the diffs from the mercurial server in
order to construct a list of files that were changed by that revision (and any
other revision pushed at the same time.)

If we are unable to retrieve the pushlog or the list of files, the test will
run anyway, under the assumption that is both safer and a more likely to be
noticed error condition than skipping the tests.

Bug 1218222 - Update to treeherder-client 1.8.0

Since we need its Hawk credential support.

pulltitle: Bug 1218222 hawk auth
pull_commit_message:
Bug 1218222 - Submit results to Treeherder's API using Hawk credentials

Treeherder now supports per-user (rather than per-repository) Hawk
credentials, which are passed directly to the TreeherderClient
constructor:
http://treeherder.readthedocs.org/submitting_data.html#authentication

Before this merges, the credentials file will need to have top-level
"client_id" and "secret" keys added. Once this is in production, the
old per-repo credentials can then be removed from the credentials file.

NB: The clocks on the machines making submissions must be accurate to
within 60 seconds to prevent authentication errors. On OS X NTP is known
to be unreliable unless tweaked, see bug 1217564.

- improve email notifications of device status.
- handle device errors on startup.
- handle tests which require device network access.
- check installation success before running tests.
- handle device errors when tearing down jobs and submitting results to Treeherder.
- reboot on unrecoverable error

pulltitle: Bug 1172585 - s3.upload() on Win 7 results in IOError
pullsbody:
Cause: "Whether the name can be used to open the file a second time, while the named temporary file is still open, varies across platforms (it can be so used on Unix; it cannot on Windows NT or later)." [1]

So I propose to let `tf` close before setting the contents of the key and then delete the temp file.

[1] https://docs.python.org/2/library/tempfile.html#tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile
pull_commit_message: Bug 1172585 - s3.upload() on Win 7 results in IOError

pullsbody:
- The test status reported to Treeherder is not set properly upon failure. Some tests which fail are being reported as Green even though job details shows an error.

Mark, I should have listened to your review feedback more and probably would have caught this.
- The  PhoneTest.job_details properly is not reinitialized when a test begins running. Previously the job_details was initialized in AutophoneTreeherder.submit_pending, but now that submit_pending is called from autophone.py when the build is first detected, and submit_running/submit_complete are called on a different when the test runs/completes, the job_details is not initialized.

Other issues which are not really regressions:
- #moc has implemented rate limiting on ftp.m.o and the utils.get_remote_text can fail due to 503 errors especially during trigger_runs.py from outside the moco network. They suggest retrying after random waits.
pull_commit_message: Bug 1147480 - Autophone - utils.get_remote_text - handle 503 Too Busy Errors

pullsbody:
Hi Mark,

I set up a fork and am using a minor issue I ran into as a learning example of how to submit patches.

I hit this when I hadn't set up the email.ini file and hit the lack of logging when the except block of

```
    try:
        from_address = cfg.get('report', 'from')
    except (ConfigParser.NoSectionError, ConfigParser.NoOptionError):
        logging.error('No "from" option defined in "report" section of file "%s".\n' % options.config_file)
        return
```

fired.
